blender render script that loads an obj exported from 3ds, scales it to a 1/1/1 box and renders (using the default settings)

each numbered subfolder contains code that works for a particular version of blender 
2.58 should work with blender 2.58



1) place 2.58/io_scene_3ds in directory ~/.blender/2.58/scripts/addons
2) startup blender
3) enable plugin
4) setup default screen
5) File->Save User Settings
6) close blender)
7) edit render_objs.py fixing the model bank and output directories
8) run script from command line: blender -P render_objs.py

1) install io_scene_3ds plugin (into <config>/scripts/addons)
on linux blender config is at ~/.blender/<version>/...
on mac blender config is at ~/Library/Application Support/Blender/<version>/...

2) startup blender
3) enable plugin
4) setup default scene (see 2.65/default.blend)
5) File->Save User Settings
6) close blender
7) edit render_objs.py fixing the model bank and output directories
8) run script from command line: blender -P render_objs.py
on mac do this in the blender.app/Contents/MacOS


